The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	Sebastian Omar Monesterolo, East Bengals new Argentine recruit reached the city on Monday evening.      
	Meanwhile, Mohun Bagan have decided to call former India player Tomba Singh for trials, but East Bengal, where he last played, said that he has to clear all dues with them before signing with a new club.       
	Bagans proposed pre-season camp at Kalimpong has run into rough weather following the indefinite bandh call in the hills.                
	 Aamer Hussain survived a scare before prevailing 3-2 over unseeded Abhishek Kedia in the BRC state senior snooker championships at the Bengal Rowing Club on Monday.      
	Top seed Manish Jain got the better of Siddharth Casyab 3-0 to advance to the third round.      
	Other results  Md Tanveer bt V. Goyal 3-0; K. Saha bt A. Dholia 3-1; D. Kothari bt W. Bhutia 3-2; N. Haldar bt V. Gupta 3-0.                
	SNOOKER: State Senior Championships at BRC from 2.15pm                                                                                                                                                                       
